title: Trespasser: Jurassic Park playthrough -- Part 2
description: Finished it up! Honestly enjoyed this game. I think the uniqueness of the weird ass arm controls over ruled the fact that the controls were bad for me. I enjoy when a game has something unique like that, and it's actually pretty fun to do stupid trick shots and play around with it. The physics work surprisingly well for 98, and although the game is very simple and the levels are a bit boring, it still kept me interested in the game the whole time. The fact that it's full of meme potential also helps.
